<TITLE> War crimes case filed in Jhenaidah </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jhenaidah, March 29 (bdnews24.com)  A freedom fighter has filed a case in Jhenaidah against six people on charges of 1971 war crimes, court officers said on Sunday. Ashir Uddin filed the case with the chief judicial magistrate's court on March 25 against Moslem Uddin, Md Abdur Rashid, Alauddin, Md Shahjahan, Md Hakim Ali Khandaker and Abdul Haque. In his statement Ashir, who left the Pakistan army in 1971 to fight for Bangladesh's independence, said some 50 collaborators led by Moslem besieged his home to capture him knowing that he had joined the freedom fighters. Failing to find him, they took his brothers Ajibor Rahman, Habibur Rahman and Ansar Uddin, he said. They shot his brothers dead near Ghoramara Bridge in Jhenaidah. Hundreds of people witnessed the killings, Ashir said in his case statement. The collaborators also beat his father, looted valuables and later set fire to the family home, said the freedom fighter. Judge Md Masudur Rahman ordered Jhenaidah Sadar police to take steps after proper investigation. bdn
